Must be enrolled in course version {2119, F20031}
(Must have passed an (I/W) unit in {FNA2111, FNA2112} and  Must have passed an (I/W) unit in {OHS1000})

proh: Any FNA, VIS or VPR level 3 unit
description: This unit is the fifth in the Contemporary Practices sequence. In this unit emphasis is placed on independent investigation, and the development of the creative and expressive potential inherent in student' work. Imagination combined with advanced conceptualisation and innovation in material manipulation should be manifest at this stage of students' practice. Whilst providing a stimulating and supportive environment this unit provides a bridge between students' experience in the supervised studio and a fully-fledged independent professional practice in the broader arts arena.
faculty: Faculty of Art, Design and Architecture
